{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566829","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566829"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:49:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:49:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18883"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18883","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18883"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.51,0.01,0.39,0.02,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11616"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79998"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11616","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11616"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18883"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65272"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11336"},{"type":"tags","id":"11337"},{"type":"tags","id":"11338"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27338"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27340"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79998","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79998"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor observes their colleague, who is also a junior doctor, making inappropriate sexual comments to patients during ward rounds. The behaviour has occurred multiple times despite previous informal discussions about professional boundaries. No physical misconduct has occurred.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next action?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Report the conduct to the medical registration board","Wait to see if the behaviour continues","Escalate to the head of department only","Document incidents for future reference only","Arrange peer mediation session"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ereport the conduct to the medical registration board\u003C/strong\u003E. Sexual misconduct, including inappropriate sexual comments to patients, is considered serious professional misconduct that requires mandatory reporting. Previous attempts to address the behaviour informally have been unsuccessful, and the conduct poses a risk to patient safety and dignity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWait to see if the behaviour continues\u003C/strong\u003E - The behaviour has already been repetitive and previous discussions have not resolved the issue\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEscalate to the head of department only\u003C/strong\u003E - While involving senior staff is important, sexual misconduct requires mandatory reporting to the registration board\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument incidents for future reference only\u003C/strong\u003E - Documentation alone is insufficient when immediate action is required to protect patients\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArrange peer mediation session\u003C/strong\u003E - Sexual misconduct is too serious for peer mediation and requires formal reporting\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare professionals have an ethical and legal obligation to report serious misconduct that puts patient safety or dignity at risk. While initial concerns should typically be discussed directly with the colleague first, when this approach has failed and the behaviour continues, formal reporting becomes necessary.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Healthcare professionals have a legal and ethical obligation to report serious misconduct that puts patient safety at risk.","Mandatory reporting requirements apply to impairment, intoxication at work, sexual misconduct, and significant departures from accepted standards.","The first step in addressing concerns about a colleague\u0027s conduct is to discuss it directly with them, unless patient safety is at immediate risk."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency. How to raise a concern about a health practitioner. [online]. n.d. [Cited 2025 Jan 16]. Available at: https://www.ahpra.gov.au/Notifications/Concerned-about-a-health-practitioner.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65272"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18883"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65272","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65272"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-16T18:54:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-16T18:54:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11616"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79998"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"